snippet.textDisplay:
I'm sick of Nolan and his cheap space-continuum gimmicks. He comes off like a first year Princeton mathematical drop-out. That sounds impressive to you but even if he were taking grad courses it's still just introductory level. It's like leaving while testing for your advanced white belt in karate.

Can he just use the regular tools and a linear plot....and do a good movie. Notice Batman Begins and Dark Knight rises he struggled with story telling because the time-plot was much more traditional.

BTW: NO!! Presitige isn't overrated. Nolan constantly using aspects of quantum physics however...is
